On International Women's Day, the President of the United States issued a statement reaffirming the country's commitment to the equality, freedom, achievements, and advancement of women. The President acknowledged the challenges the world faces, such as climate change, poverty, and conflict, and emphasized the importance of women's participation in finding solutions. Women are recognized for their leadership roles in various fields, including health, education, business, and science. The President expressed hope that all daughters, both in the United States and around the world, will have the opportunity to become leaders and achieve their full potential. The statement also highlighted the celebration and honor of women's sacrifices, talents, and leadership.